minaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/09\/05\/masjid-prayer-twenty-seven-better\/","url_meta":{"origin":14904,"position":0},"title":"Hadith on Jama&#8217;ah: Prayer in mosque is twenty seven times better","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"September 5, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdullah ibn Umar reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cPrayer in congregation is better than prayer alone by twenty-seven degrees.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 645, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 650 Grade: Muttafaqun Alayhi (authenticity agreed upon) according to Al-Bukhari and Muslim Ibn Qudamah said, \"Congregational prayer is\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":27566,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/04\/15\/permission-not-fast-journey\/","url_meta":{"origin":14904,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Travel: Permission to fast or not on journey, whatever is easiest","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"April 15, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: Hamzah ibn Amr asked the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, about fasting while traveling. The Prophet said, \u201cIf you wish, you may fast. And if you wish, you may break your fast.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 1841, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 1121 Grade: Muttafaqun Alayhi (authenticity agreed\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25503,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/12\/01\/bismillah-begin-salat\/","url_meta":{"origin":14904,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Bismillah: Reciting name of Allah to begin prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 1, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, as well as Abu Bakr and Umar, may Allah be pleased with them, would open the prayer by reciting, \u201cAll praise is due to Allah.\u201d (1:1) In the narration of Muslim, Anas said: I did not hear any of them\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":33326,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/08\/31\/fasting-ashura-9th-muharram\/","url_meta":{"origin":14904,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on &#8216;Ashura: Fasting day of &#8216;Ashura with 9th of Muharram","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 31, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Al-Hakam ibn al-A\u2019raj reported: I went to Ibn Abbas, may Allah be pleased with him, and I said, \u201cTell me about fasting the day of 'Ashura.\u201d Ibn Abbas said, \u201cWhen you see the crescent of the month of al-Muharram, count the days and wake up to fast on the ninth\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":12088,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/02\/06\/eating-dinner-maghrib-prayer\/","url_meta":{"origin":14904,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Prayer: Eating dinner before Maghrib prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"February 6, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas ibn Malik reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cIf dinner is presented close to the time of prayer, begin eating before you perform sunset prayer and do not need to rush away from your dinner.\" Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 640, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 558 Grade:\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":15098,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/07\/16\/niyyah-obligatory-sawm\/","url_meta":{"origin":14904,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Fasting: Making intention before days of obligatory fasting","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 16, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Hafsa reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhoever does not have the intention to fast before dawn, there is no fasting for him.\u201d Al-Tirmidhi said, \"The meaning according to the people of knowledge is that the fast is invalid if intention is not made before sunrise\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/14904","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyh